# specwatch-ignore — patterns to suppress from stale-reference reports
#
# Format:
#   - One pattern per line
#   - Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored
#   - Patterns use .gitignore-style globs (*, **, ?)
#   - Each pattern is matched against three fields for every stale reference:
#       1. Source file path (repo-relative, e.g., docs/epic/Active/...)
#       2. Broken link target (the raw href from the markdown link)
#       3. Artifact ID (e.g., EPIC-001, ADR-003)
#   - If ANY field matches ANY pattern, the stale reference is suppressed
#
# Examples:
#   docs/archive/*          # ignore all files under docs/archive/
#   LEGACY-*                # ignore any artifact ID starting with LEGACY-
#   */scratch/*             # ignore links in or to scratch directories
#   *.draft.md              # ignore draft markdown files

# Template/guide files contain example links from other projects that
# will never resolve in this repo. These are illustrative, not real refs.
docs/templates/*

# Abandoned specs from the pre-EPIC-007 cross-source rewrite plan.
# These were superseded by EPIC-007 restructuring + SPEC-018 statistics
# update. Their frontmatter still references each other and unresolvable
# specs, but they are frozen historical records — not worth fixing.
docs/spec/(SPEC-005)-*
docs/spec/(SPEC-006)-*
docs/spec/(SPEC-007)-*
docs/spec/(SPEC-008)-*
docs/spec/(SPEC-009)-*
